Coordinate reference systems
fields.description: Systems for uniquely referencing spatial information in space as a set of coordinates (x,y,z) and/or latitude and longitude and height, based on a geodetic horizontal and vertical datum

fields.name: Geographical grid systems
fields.description: Harmonised multi-resolution grid with a common point of origin and standardised location and size of grid cells

fields.name: Geographical names
fields.description: Names of areas, regions, localities, cities, suburbs, towns or settlements, or any geographical or topographical feature of public or historical interest

fields.name: Administrative units
fields.description: Units of administration, dividing areas where Member States have and/or exercise jurisdictional rights, for local, regional and national governance, separated by administrative boundaries

fields.name: Addresses
fields.description: Location of properties based on address identifiers, usually by road name, house number, postal code

fields.name: Cadastral parcels
fields.description: Areas defined by cadastral registers or equivalent

fields.name: Transport networks
fields.description: Road, rail, air and water transport networks and related infrastructure. Includes links between different networks. Also includes the trans-European transport network as defined in Decision 1692/96/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 23 July 1996 on Community guidelines for the development of the trans-European transport network and future revisions of that decision

fields.name: Hydrography
fields.description: Hydrographic elements, including marine areas and all other water bodies and items related to them, including river basins and sub-basins. Where appropriate, according to the definitions set out in Directive 2000/60/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 23 October 2000 establishing a framework for Community action in the field of water policy, and in the form of networks

fields.name: Protected sites
fields.description: Area designated or managed within a framework of international, Community and Member States' legislation to achieve specific conservation objectives

fields.name: Elevation
fields.description: Digital elevation models for land, ice and ocean surfaces. Includes terrestrial elevation, bathymetry and shoreline

fields.name: Land cover
fields.description: Physical and biological cover of the earth's surface including artificial surfaces, agricultural areas, forests, (semi-)natural areas, wetlands, water bodies

fields.name: Orthoimagery
fields.description: Geo-referenced image data of the Earth's surface, from either satellite or airborne sensors

fields.name: Geology
fields.description: Geology characterised according to composition and structure. Includes bedrock, aquifers and geomorphology

fields.name: Statistical units
fields.description: Units for dissemination or use of statistical information

fields.name: Buildings
fields.description: Geographical location of buildings

fields.name: Soil
fields.description: Soils and subsoil characterised according to depth, texture, structure and content of particles and organic material, stoniness, erosion, where appropriate mean slope and anticipated water storage capacity

fields.name: Land use
fields.description: Territory characterised according to its current and future planned functional dimension or socio–economic purpose (e.g. residential, industrial, commercial, agricultural, forestry, recreational)

fields.name: Human health and safety
fields.description: Geographical distribution of dominance of pathologies (allergies, cancers, respiratory diseases, etc.), information indicating the effect on health ( biomarkers, decline of fertility, epidemics) or well-being of humans (fatigue, stress, etc.) linked directly (air pollution, chemicals, depletion of the ozone layer, noise, etc.) or indirectly (food, genetically modified organisms, etc.) to the quality of the environment

fields.name: Utility and governmental services
fields.description: Includes utility facilities such as sewage, waste management, energy supply and water supply, administrative and social governmental services such as public administrations, civil protection sites, schools and hospitals

fields.name: Environmental monitoring facilities
fields.description: Location and operation of environmental monitoring facilities includes observation and measurement of emissions, of the state of environmental media and of other ecosystem parameters (biodiversity, ecological conditions of vegetation, etc.) by or on behalf of public authorities

fields.name: Production and industrial facilities
fields.description: Industrial production sites, including installations covered by Directive 96/61/EC of 24 September 1996 concerning integrated pollution prevention and control and water abstraction facilities, mining, storage sites

fields.name: Agricultural and aquaculture facilities
fields.description: Farming equipment and production facilities (including irrigation systems, greenhouses and stables)

fields.name: Population distribution and demography
fields.description: Geographical distribution of people, including population characteristics and activity levels, aggregated by grid, region, administrative unit or other analytical unit

fields.name: Area management/restriction/regulation zones & reporting units
fields.description: Areas managed, regulated or used for reporting at international, European, national, regional and local levels. Includes dumping sites, restricted areas around drinking water sources, nitrate-vulnerable zones, regulated fairways at sea or large inland waters, areas for the dumping of waste, noise restriction zones, prospecting and mining permit areas, river basin districts, relevant reporting units and coastal zone management areas

fields.name: Natural risk zones
fields.description: Vulnerable areas characterised according to natural hazards (all atmospheric, hydrologic, seismic, volcanic and wildfire phenomena that, because of their location, severity, and frequency, have the potential to seriously affect society), e.g. floods, landslides and subsidence, avalanches, forest fires, earthquakes, volcanic eruptions

fields.name: Atmospheric conditions
fields.description: Physical conditions in the atmosphere. Includes spatial data based on measurements, on models or on a combination thereof and includes measurement locations

fields.name: Meteorological geographical features
fields.description: Weather conditions and their measurements; precipitation, temperature, evapotranspiration, wind speed and direction

fields.name: Oceanographic geographical features
fields.description: Physical conditions of oceans (currents, salinity, wave heights, etc.)

fields.name: Sea regions
fields.description: Physical conditions of seas and saline water bodies divided into regions and sub-regions with common characteristics

fields.name: Bio-geographical regions
fields.description: Areas of relatively homogeneous ecological conditions with common characteristics

fields.name: Habitats and biotopes
fields.description: Geographical areas characterised by specific ecological conditions, processes, structure, and (life support) functions that physically support the organisms that live there. Includes terrestrial and aquatic areas distinguished by geographical, abiotic and biotic features, whether entirely natural or semi-natural

fields.name: Species distribution
fields.description: Geographical distribution of occurrence of animal and plant species aggregated by grid, region, administrative unit or other analytical unit

fields.name: Energy resources
fields.description: Energy resources including hydrocarbons, hydropower, bio-energy, solar, wind, etc., where relevant including depth/height information on the extent of the resource

fields.name: Mineral resources
fields.description: Mineral resources including metal ores, industrial minerals, etc., where relevant including depth/height information on the extent of the resource

fields.parameter: Carbon Dioxide, Methane and other long-lived greenhouse gases

fields.name: Essential
fields.description: Product specifications will not be met if essential data are unavailable.

fields.name: Desirable
fields.description: Availability of data could improve the product. Data are included for redundancy purposes

fields.name: Useful
fields.description: Additional in situ data not directly linked to product generation, validation or calibration are considered as useful.
